browserforce:apply.description: apply a plan from a plan file or remote state
examples:
$ sfdx browserforce:apply -f ./config/setup-admin-login-as-any.json --targetusername myOrg@example.com
  Applying plan file ./config/setup-admin-login-as-any.json to org myOrg@example.com
  logging in... done
  [LoginAccessPolicies] retrieving state... done
  [LoginAccessPolicies] changing 'administratorsCanLogInAsAnyUser' to 'true'... done
  logging out... done

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

targetusername.name: targetusername
targetusername.description: username or alias for the target org; overrides default target org

apiversion.name: apiversion
apiversion.description: override the api version used for api requests made by this command

definitionfile.name: definitionfile
definitionfile.description:
path to a browserforce definition file
The schema is similar to the scratch org definition file.
See https://github.com/amtrack/sfdx-browserforce-plugin#supported-org-preferences for supported values.

planfile.name: planfile
planfile.description: path to a browserforce plan file

statefile.name: statefile
statefile.description: path to a browserforce state file

browserforce:plan.description: retrieve state and generate plan file
examples:
$ sfdx browserforce:plan -f ./config/setup-admin-login-as-any.json -o /tmp/state.json --targetusername myOrg@example.com
  Generating plan with definition file ./config/setup-admin-login-as-any.json from org myOrg@example.com
  logging in... done
  [LoginAccessPolicies] retrieving state... done
  [LoginAccessPolicies] generating plan... done
  logging out... done
